**No, you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** on .NET 10. That property is the .NET 9 (and earlier) shim. On .NET 10, native MTP support is configured via `global.json`.

Add a `"test"` section to your `global.json`:

```json
{
  "sdk": {
    "version": "10.0.100"
  },
  "test": {
    "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"
  }
}
```

Then remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from your `.csproj` — it's unnecessary and ignored.

